'''Banjul American Embassy School''' ('''BAES''') is an American [[international school]] in the [[Banjul]] area of [[the Gambia]]. It serves preschool through high school.
American parents established the school in January 1984 after feeling dissatisfied with the education in the [[Marina International School]], which previously educated American children.<ref>"[http://baes.gm/history History]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Y5tSA0yE Archive]). Banjul American Embassy School. Retrieved April 27, 2015.</ref> The BAES high school began operations in 2012.<ref>"[http://baes.gm/high-school High School]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Y5u0Cdlf Archive]). Banjul American Embassy School. Retrieved April 27, 2015.</ref> The [[University of Nebraska–Lincoln]] provides high school [[correspondence course]]s to students at BAES.<ref>"[https://www.state.gov/m/a/os/219578.htm Gambia, Banjul: Banjul American Embassy School]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6Y5uBJr4N Archive]). [[U.S. State Department]]. Retrieved April 27, 2015.</ref>
