The '''Forecasting Division of Western Norway''' ({{lang-no|Vêrvarslinga på Vestlandet}}) is a department of the [[Norwegian Meteorological Institute]] located in [[Bergen]]. It was established in 1918.<ref name=snl/> It prepares weather forecasting for the area between [[Nord-Trøndelag]] and [[Lista, Norway|Lista]], as well as the fishing grounds around [[The British Isles]] and [[Iceland]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vervarslinga på Vestlandet|url=http://met.no/Om_oss/?module=Articles;action=Article.publicShow;ID=272#|publisher=[[Norwegian Meteorological Institute]]|accessdate=11 March 2011|language=Norwegian}}</ref>
