'''HMS ''Scimitar''''' is a {{sclass-|Scimitar|patrol vessel|0}} [[patrol boat|fast patrol boat]] of the [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Royal Navy]]. She is a Lifespan Patrol Vessel type boat and formerly served in inland waterway duties in [[Northern Ireland]] as MV ''Grey Fox''. She was acquired to serve with the [[Gibraltar Squadron]], tasked with policing, customs and [[search and rescue]] duties. This released an {{sclass-|Archer|patrol vessel|0}} patrol vessel for tasking with the [[Cyprus Squadron]].
==Operational history== ''Scimitar'' was involved in a diplomatic incident between the United Kingdom and Spain in November 2009 after being alleged by the Spanish to have been using the Spanish flag as a target during gunnery practice. The [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]] stated that the ship had actually been shooting at a [[NATO]] maritime signal flag, which is similar in appearance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/europe/8371305.stm |title=UK 'sorry' for shooting at 'Spanish flag' buoy.|accessdate=2009-12-31|date=November 2009|publisher=British Broadcasting Corporation}}</ref>
On 3 May 2011 ''Scimitar'' was dispatched to intercept the Spanish {{sclass-|Serviola|patrol boat|0}} patrol boat {{ship|Spanish patrol boat|Atalaya|P74|2}} when she entered British waters (claimed by Spanish) around Gibraltar and ordered the Spanish ship to leave the area.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://defensenews.com/story.php?i=6403538&c=SEA&s=EUR|title=Gibraltar Slams New 'Incursion' By Spanish Navy.|accessdate=2011-05-10|date=May 2011|publisher=Defence News}}</ref> ''Scimitar'' took part in another encounter with a Spanish naval vessel on 4 April 2017. It challenged ''Infanta Cristina,'' a {{sclass-|Descubierta|corvette}} that had entered British waters (claimed by Spanish) off of Gibraltar. ''Infanta Cristina'' left without further incident.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/04/04/new-spanish-patrol-boat-incursion-gibraltars-waters/?WT.mc_id=tmgoff_fb_tmg|title=Royal Navy chases Spanish patrol boat out of waters off Gibraltar as Nigel Farage says UK must not be 'bullied'.|accessdate=2017-04-04|date=April 2017|publisher=The Telegraph}}</ref>
On 8 November 2017, HMS ''Scimitar'' intercepted the Spanish corvette ''Infanta Elena'' trying to enter British territorial waters off Gibraltar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ukdefencejournal.org.uk/spanish-warship-forced-away-gibraltar-patrol-boat-hms-scimitar |title=Spanish warship forced away from Gibraltar by patrol boat HMS Scimitar.|accessdate=2017-08-11|date=November 2017|publisher=UK Defence Journal}}</ref>
==Replacement== In July 2017 it was revealed that the Gibraltar Squadron would receive two new warships which will be more “capable”, “faster” and have “bigger guns”, to replace ''Sabre'' and ''Scimitar'' "within the next two years".<ref>http://www.gbc.gi/news/gibraltar-squadron-receive-two-new-warships</ref>
