{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
The '''Karamogo''' were the scholar class among the peaceful [[Dyula people|Dyula]] [[merchant|traders]] of [[Western Africa]], of which [[Al-Hajj Salim Suwari]] was a prominent member. The Karamogo developed theological rationales for living among non-[[Muslim]]s, arguing that one should nurture one's own faith and let conversion happen in its own time. Accordingly, [[jihad]] should not be waged except in defensive contexts.

