The '''Diocese of Frigento''' (Latin: ''Dioecesis Frequentina'') was a Roman Catholic diocese located in the town of [[Frigento]] in the [[province of Avellino]], [[Campania]], [[Italy]]. In 1466, it was united with the [[Diocese of Avellino]] to form the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Avellino|Diocese of Avellino e Frigento]].<ref name=CathHierFrigento>{{Cite web|last=Cheney |first=David M.|authorlink=|title=Diocese of Frigento |publisher=''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/df513.html  |accessdate=June 16, 2018}} [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref><ref name=GCathFrigento>{{Cite web|last=Chow |first=Gabriel|authorlink=|title=Titular Episcopal See of Frigento |publisher=''[[GCatholic.org]]''|date=|url=http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0815.htm |accessdate=June 16, 2018}} [[Wikipedia:SPS|{{sup|[''self-published'']}}]]</ref> It was restored as a Titular Episcopal See in 1970.<ref name=GCathFrigento />

