{{Infobox prepared food | name = Sobolo | image = File:Sobolo.jpg | caption = Bottles of sobolo | alternate_name = Bissap | country = [[Ghana]] | region = Northern | creator = | course = Biscuit,Cake | served = Cold Ice | main_ingredient = [[Bissap]] Leaves, Water, Sugar, Ginger, | variations = | calories = | other = }}
'''Sobolo''' is the [[Ghanaian]] name for a drink made out of rosella leaves, it is referred to with different names in different countries where the drink can be found, but it is generally referred to as Bissap.<ref name=infobox>{{cite web|url=http://infoboxdaily.com/life/your-food/item/1470-sobolo-bissap-drink|title=Sobolo (Bissap Drink)|accessdate=19 March 2015}}</ref>
==Overview== Sobolo is a cool drink found in most West African countries. It is a dark red-purple coloured juice. The [[Burkina Faso|Burkinabes]] call it bissap while the [[Ghanaian]]s, Nigeriens, Burkinabe and [[Nigerian]]s call it sobolo. It tastes a bit grapey and a little bit like cranberry juice and can be served with mint leaves.<ref name=infobox />It can also be served with any flavouring of one's choice; sometimes with pineapple juice, tea grass, vanilla and many others.
==Preparation== Sobolo is prepared using water, Bissap flowers, sugar and ginger. *Wash your Bissap flowers in clean disinfect water *After that, put flowers into water and allow to boil, or soak overnight. *Remove from fire and allow to cool, then drain with a strainer to separate leaves from coloured water *You may add pineapple juice at this point. If tea grass, you can boil together with the leaves. * inpour if you boiled, or j the rainre,pocolou ed you ereif . ri nk *Allow to cool if it is still hot, then refrigerate and serve refrigera te *and serve
