'''St Volodymyr Chapel''' (properly '''Grand Prince St. Vladimir, Equal-to-the-Apostles''') is a small Eastern Orthodox Chapel which serves the Vernadsky Research Base on Galindez Island, Antarctica. It is one of eight [[List of Antarctic churches|churches]] in Antarctica.
The chapel, a simple wooden construction, was built on the island in 2011. Its creation was funded by philanthropists. It was consecrated by the Archbishop of Lviv and Galicia.<ref>{{cite web|title=Worldwide Antarctic Program|URL=http://www.waponline.it/st-volodymyr-chapel-at-ukrainian-vernadsky-base/ |accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref> Despite its small size, the chapel is richly decorated. Its contents include an icon of St Nicholas.<ref>{{cite web|title=Polar News|URL=https://polar-news.com/antarctic/society/174-faith-in-antarctica-religion-in-the-land-of-eternal-snow |accessdate=14 February 2018}}</ref>
