The '''Taipei Chinese Orchestra''' ('''TCO'''; {{zh|t=臺北市立國樂團|p=Táiběishì Lìguó Yuètuán}}) is a [[Chinese orchestra]] based in [[Zhongzheng District]], [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]], [[Republic of China]] as the first professional ensemble of its kind in Taiwan.<ref>{{cite web|title=Orchestra history|url=http://www.tco.taipei.gov.tw/ct.asp?xItem=1109744&CtNode=7091&mp=119041|publisher=Taipei Chinese Orchestra|accessdate=1 July 2013}}</ref>

==History==
In 1979, '''Taipei Chinese Orchestra''' was founded by [[Taipei City Government]].<ref>[http://english.tco.taipei.gov.tw/ct.asp?xItem=664465&CtNode=10877&mp=119042 The Orchestra’s History]，Source: Taipei Chinese Orchestra</ref>

Until 6 November 1999, [[Taipei City Government]] established the Department of Cultural Affairs, then '''Taipei Chinese Orchestra''' was belong to Department of Cultural Affairs, Taipei City Government.

