{{Italic title}} {{Infobox book | name = The Siege | title_orig = Kështjella | translator = [[David Bellos]] | image = The Siege (Kadare novel).jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = Albanian cover | author = [[Ismail Kadare]] | country = Albania | language = Albanian | genre = [[History]] | publisher = [[Sh.B. Naim Frashëri]] | publisher2 = [[Canongate Books]] | pub_date = 1970 | english_pub_date = 2008 | media_type = | pages = {{flagicon|Albania}} 304 {{flagicon|US}} 328 | isbn = 0-8021-4475-6 | oclc = }}
'''''The Siege''''' (also known as '''''The Castle''''') is a novel by Albanian author [[Ismail Kadare]], first published in 1970 in [[Tirana]] as ''Kështjella''. It tells about the [[League of Lezhë|Albanian-Ottoman war]] during the time of [[Skanderbeg]]. It was translated into French by Jusuf Vrioni and then from French into English by [[David Bellos]] under the title ''The Siege''.<ref name=Gibson>{{Cite news|newspaper=[[The Globe and Mail]]|title=New life for a novelist's early work|first=Brian|last=Gibson|date=Jan 23, 2009|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/arts/books-and-media/new-life-for-a-novelists-early-work/article1147216/}}</ref> Bellos in his afterword suggests that the book is patterned after [[Marin Barleti]]'s work ''[[The Siege of Shkodra (book)|The Siege of Shkodra]]''.<ref>{{cite book|last=Kadare|first=Ismail|title=The Siege|year=2008|publisher=[[Canongate Books]]|isbn=978-1-84767-185-1|pages=324–328}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/kadare.htm |title=Ismail Kadare |website=Books and Writers ''(kirjasto.sci.fi)'' |first=Petri |last=Liukkonen |publisher=[[Kuusankoski]] Public Library |location=Finland |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150113052232/http://www.kirjasto.sci.fi/kadare.htm |archivedate=13 January 2015 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The narrator of the novel is however not an Albanian but a member of the besieging Turkish army.<ref name=Gibson />
